summary: Email chain among law enforcement and prosecutors regarding rescheduling an interview with an individual named Mullen and coordinating the review and submission of a draft affidavit for an amended search warrant for drives seized from Jeffrey Epstein's New York residence.

persons.name: Mullen
persons.context: An interview with Mullen was scheduled and then canceled; law enforcement is seeking to reschedule it for later in the week.

events.title: Interview with Mullen canceled
events.description: A law enforcement detective canceled an interview with Mullen and is awaiting a response to reschedule it for later in the week.

events.title: Draft affidavit for amended warrant submitted
events.description: An Assistant United States Attorney sent a draft affidavit in support of an amended search warrant for three drives seized from Jeffrey Epstein's New York residence to law enforcement for review.

keyFacts: Law enforcement was actively working on obtaining an amended search warrant for digital drives seized from Jeffrey Epstein's New York residence as of October 2020.
An interview with an individual named Mullen was part of the investigative activities and was being rescheduled.
The correspondence involves coordination between the NYPD, FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force, and the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York.
The document indicates ongoing post-mortem investigation into Epstein's activities, specifically focusing on evidence from his New York home.
